description: Stormwatch is gathered and prepared, all but Jenny Sparks, to take on The High and his team, who are called the Changers. They infiltrate the Changer's base and attack swiftly and thoroughly. Meanwhile, Jenny Sparks finally gets to speak to Henry Bendix, demanding answers about the recent happenings. While Stormwatch and The Changers fight, Jenny Sparks learns that Henry Bendix is crazy, wanting to control the world in his own vision and the Changers, with their plans, would interfere with his own. Jenny Sparks kills him and tries to stop a Stormwatch crew to drop weapons on the Changers but it's too late: the Changers are killed, except for The High. The High speeds straight into space, believing that Bendix is still alive, and plans to demolish Skywatch. Jenny Sparks is forced to erect a force field, killing The High.
name: Change Or Die: Part Three Of Three

description:
The issue starts with a huge explosion on some kind of mysterious space craft. The scene then cuts to the ever-joyfilled Stan Lee, who tells the readers that every issue should start out with an explosion- so the writers don't have to do any dialogue. He then goes on to look for Zenn-La, the Silver Surfer's home planet, before stepping down and into the hallowed halls of Marvel.

As Stan walks down the hallway, numerous statues of famous Marvel characters, such as Hulk, Namor, Black Bolt, Spider-Woman, and more line the walls, and he tells you that you should know all of them-or leave. He then goes to an area in which the Fantastic Four are being built, commenting on how their look changes to often for the artists to get a clear image of them.

Walking further, he sees a statue of Professor Xavier, and tells how he created the X-Men. He then walks down the halls more, showing the readers numerous statues of other famous X-Men during their time such as Mohawk Storm and the original X-Men team. He then tells the reader he has a suprise about the formation of the team, and activates a flashback with a scream.

The scene is of a young, red haired girl named Jean Grey, as she kneels in her room, praying. Her father walks in and catches her praying. Jean tells him how much Professor Xavier has helped since the accident with her friend Annie, and John Grey mentally thanks the Professor for helping Jean get over this. She observes a shooting star before going to sleep.

That shooting star is not exactly what is appears to be, and it lands in barn. where a cloaked figure falls out of it, complaining about how rough time travel is. It is revealed to be Rachel Summers, the future daughter of Jean Grey. She says how she has followed someone to this location, and she walks around for a minute, before seeing the ominous figure of Master Mold towering above her. As she looks at it, she realizes why she's there.

The images then go to a young man's mind, where he is dreaming of the future X-Men and Senator Robert Kelly and his importance. His father, Bolivar Trask blames himself for his son's detoriorating condition, and lets him rest. He then observes his family before Larry wakes up. Larry is given excuses to why he has been sleeping, and he believes his father.

As Larry wanders outside of the barn, Rachel is observing him, using her psychic abilities to make him believe that she is not there. After a few moments, she is attacked by Sanctity, one of her disciples. The two duke it out, until when Rachel attacks her, it is revealed that this Sanctity was just a psychic echo of the real one, who is inside the lab.

Sanctity is visiting with her father, Bolivar. As she talks with him, Rachel completely erases every memory of the beginning of the conversation. While Sancitity is upset, she understands. Her and Rachel leave an unconcious Bolivar and and clueless Larry to go back to their rightful time.

In the end of the book, Stan Lee calls cut and the issue is coming to an end. After warning the readers about a possible quiz, he says he has to leave, and goes out with his usual 'Excelsior'!
name: The Boy Who Saw Tomorrow !

description:
PKNA #7

Invasione! / Invasion!
name: Invasione!

description: Luse attempts to flee Sanctuary after the events of recent issues.
name: Five: Walking Spanish Down The Hall

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 4: Strange Days One: No New Tale To Tell

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 4: Strange Days One: No New Tale To Tell

description:
General Notes

Alex says the last time he stood atop the World Trade Center was in 2004 but due to the events that would happen between the publication of this issue (1997) and the date used as a point of reference (2004), the story lost a point of connection to the real world as on September 11, 2001 the World Trade Center towers (which as mentioned in the story were the tallest buildings in the world at one point) were brought down by two hi-jacked planes intentionally flown into them.
name: Lust For Life part 3 of 3

deck: Supergirl tries to be Silver Banshee's friend, but... it doesn't work out as well as she would have hoped.
description:
Silver Banshee, accidently freed by Supergirl, wanders Leesburg in a daze until a police attack reminds her of who she is, and she fights back.

The Silver Banshee can only kill you if she knows your name. Unfortunately cops wear namebadges...
name: Sound And Fury

description:
Titania, lost in the fog that was created from the dissipation of Faerie, sees a small girl, who introduces herself as Mary Rose. Titania says she once knew a girl with that name, before she betrayed her.

The girl wants to take her back to her house, but Titania makes a fairy illusion for them to play in. The girl recognizes her as a Faerie, and is scared.

Huon tells Tim that he has not destroyed Faerie, merely turned it inchoate, so that it may take a new shape, as its still-living inhabitants wish.

Auberon comes upon a figure in the form of Gwendolyn, who reproaches him for his cowardice in the face of the Teind, as well as in his relationship with Titania.

Huon explains that Lucifer created Hell out of an empty space, as he wished it to be, just as Faerie is now to be created by wishes.

Molly comes upon another version of herself, who berates her for letting herself fall for Taik, and for letting her anger get the better of her. She wants her to trust herself again.

Taik's true soul comes upon the spirit who had taken over his body in the fog, naming him Abaddon, one of the powerful demons of Hell. He had slowly wormed his way into Taik's once-pure soul, who did in truth love Molly. The two selves fight, and Abaddon kills Taik, but is himself then stomped to death by his horse.

Yarrow meets herself as well, and decides she must follow Molly's example, and be herself no matter what. She is the new Fool of the Forthing, now that the Amadan is gone.

Huon explains that everyone is by themselves, and must find themselves, and thus recreate Faerie. Tim, however, says we find ourselves by being with other people, and decides that its time for him to be an Opener: he will open all to the world.

However, Huon says that Yarrow has born the world without him: she is the Leveller. He sends Tim home. Huon says that Faerie no longer has to pay the Teind, and that Taik has been returned in the shape of a horse, but without his demon-parasite.

Yarrow tells all the fairies that Molly's example is what saved them, and recreated their realm. Titania can't fix Molly, since she ate fairy food, but she says she can go home and walk above the earth, and eat from a bag of fairy food, and thus survive. They send her home as well.

Auberon and Titania resolve to work harder at living together truthfully.

Huon is back in his realm. He still does not know who he is.
name: Rites of Passage, Conclusion: A World of One

description: A father believes he has gotten away from his old life of crime. That is, until evidence that a manical murderer that hates him is on the move...
Superman and Lois Lane guest star.
name: Triage

description: Scarecrow continued to torment Dick - his fears and under-self-confidence got to him. He worked through it and put the crunch on Professor Crane.
name: The Neighborhood

description: It's a day in the life of the Legion, largely told through the journal entries of Science Cop Shvaughn Erin, who becomes reflective after realizing just how different she is from these "kids" with whom she's trapped in the 20th century.

Overview

The mystery of the plundered graves leads Hellboy to a million gallons of boiling human fat and the unnatural birth of the God of Science. In Gary Gianni's "Autopsy in B-Flat," St. George is buried alive alongside the stolen treasure of squidheaded pirates.
name: Almost Colossus, Part 2; Autopsu in B-Flat, Part 2

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: Lost beyond the stars that empower him, Nexus must fight his way through a giant space amoeba and find his way home! Join Eisner Award-winning team Mike Baron and Steve Rude as they take their popular character Nexus back to his roots in this dramatic, black-and-white miniseries. This issue features a special guest appearance by First Comics' cult hero Grimjack!

name: The Hero

description: Is John Irons guilty of murder? With all the evidence pointing in that direction, it looks like the only steel he's going to know in the future is the kind that prison bars are made of.
Ninjak battles against the most powerful war machine in the universe! Place your bets!
One time Shadowman Jack Boniface is back from the Deadside and is looking to take a piece out of Zero's hide. And Zero goes looking for a little distraction from the madhouse his life has become.
name: Nothing Is True Part Two

description: OverviewTarzan encounters the concrete jungle! New York's scientific community is fighting over rights to the notebooks of Dr. Victor von Frankenstein, and the jungle lord finds himself pulled into the middle of the fray when a hulking monster figures into the mix. This issue features Thomas Edison, Nikola Tesla, Arthur Conan Doyle, and Frankenstein's monster!
name: The Modern Prometheus (Part 1 of 2)

description: The gods Izanagi and Izanami gave birth to the islands of Japan, and to the rivers, the mountains, and the trees. They gave birth to the Sun Goddess, Amaterasu, and to the Moon God, Tsukiyomi. But it is with their third child, Susano-o the Storm God, that this adventure truly begins, for it was Susano-o who slayed the eight-headed serpent, and in that serpent's tail that Susano-o discovered the great sword known as Grasscutter.
name: Grasscutter, Prologue

description:
The Joker and the Demon decide to forget about Gotham City and concentrate instead on their common enemy: Batman.

Bruce Wayne had a date with Vesper Fairchild, but it ended with the light of the Batsignal. Joker cooked up some gas that turned people into subservient zombies with his trademark smile. Batman chased down Joker and Etrigan.
name: Major Arcana, Part 2: Night of the Dying Jokers

description: The Riddler has kidnapped Commissioner Gordon. Can Batman solve the battery of clues in time to save his life? And is Batgirl's involvement a help or a hindrance?
name: Why is a Raven Like a Writing Desk?

description: The hunt for the Magician draws to a close in the conclusion to the Dirty Tricks storyline.
name: Dirty Tricks: Part 3 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Morella, the leader of an international crime syndicate, recruits Catwoman to the fold. But when Selina learns what kind of inhuman horror her new boss is, she decides to destroy the syndicate instead.
name: Trapped in the Web of Morella

description: Clay, Brenda, Marlon and Kenn investigate incidents where aircraft disappear and reappear in an instant.
name: Last Days - Part One

description:
Flash returns to Keystone City to take on the menace of the soulless Rogue's Gallery that are intent on destroying first his city.

Part 2 of "Hell To Pay" guest starring the JLA as Flash goes to hell literally to deal with Neron, then returns to Keystone City to take on the soulless Rogues Gallery intent on destroying first his city and then... him!
name: Hearts and Souls

description: Suburban angst takes on a whole new meaning when a motley gang of angry spirits descends on a South London borough. All hell breaks loose--and for once, John Constantine isn't to blame. "Widdershins" part 1.
name: Widdershins, Part 1

description: Arrowette faces off the Spazz in Manchester.
name: Arrowette vs. The Spazz

description: In the conclusion of "Time Machine Go," a veritable blood bath ensues as King Mob takes on a pair of Japanese gangsters. Meanwhile, Lord Fanny, Jack and a new trio of decadently dressed Invisibles embark on a quest for a bizarre artifact--and hasten the apocalypse in the process.
name: The Sound Of The Atom Splitting

description: Billy Batson is drawn into an inter-dimensional struggle led by a crusading rabbit? Hoppy the Marvel Bunny makes his way into Captain Marvel's Universe--and why not? It is Billy's birthday!
name: Watch Me Pull A Rabbit Out Of My Hat!

description:
Starr copes with his latest physical disaster, Jesse and Tulip attempt to reconcile their relationship, and Cassidy struggles to live with the results of his recent stupidity. Plus, Jesse's search for God intensifies.

Tulip tries to figure out how to handle Cassidy's confession, and begins to suspect that his promise to Jesse might have an ulterior motive; Starr tries on hats.

__

Our issue begins with Cassidy coming to grips with the fact he's the "biggest wanker in the entire world". The scene cuts to Tulip in bed with Jesse, laying there thinking about Cass's confession and explaining to Jesse why she felt so betrayed when he left her in France.

Meanwhile

Herr Starr begins trying on wigs. but decides to switch to hats when he realizes all the wigs look awful. Finally he finds a fedora of sorts which not only looks good but covers up the nasty scar from Jesse slitting his head open.

Elsewhere.

Cass, Jesse, Tulip and Amy all meet for a drink. Jesse gets up to have a dance with Amy while Tulip and Cass talk about his recent confession. Later on, Tulip and Amy leave to a more feminine place while Cass and Jesse get into a bar-fight of sorts.

Amy leaves and tells Tulip to call her if she ever needs her.

The book ends with The Saint of Killers off in the desert with few words left on his lips...

"War it is"
name: Rumors Of War

description: "The Crone" part 1! Manhattanites are riveted to their radios for the exciting new serial drama, "The Coming Of Night." But as tensions flare in the real lives of the show's cast, its outrageous plots take second stage to the shocking murders that befall its performers!
name: The Crone, Act One of Four

description: To conclude his inquiry into the Jim Corrigan mystery, Nate Kane may have to face a berserk Spectre.
name: The Haunting of Jim Corrigan - Conclusion: Forgiveness!

description:
Solomon Grundy lies dying and now Jack Knight, Batman, Sentinel, and the Floronic Man must band together to save the reformed criminal. However, to save the pale giant, they must face past incarnations of Grundy, all of which are evil to the core.

Infernal Devices: Part 4 of 4 seems like such a misnomer. This is more of an interlude, wherein Ted calls in few favors from Alan Scott, Batman and the Floronic Man who join Jack on a fantastic journey inside the comatose Solomon Grundy!
name: With Some Help from His Friends (Infernal Devices Interlude)

description: When Superman action figures get distributed to kids of Metropolis, the little toys seem like an innocent gift. But when money and jewelry start disappearing from homes across Metropolis, these toys may actually be playing a dangerous game!
name: Don't Try This at Home

description: In the depths of hell, side-by-side with Artemis, Wonder Woman must face her greatest challenge…and the ultimate tragedy! Featuring the demonic villainy of Neron!
name: All My Sins Remembered

description: A serial killer is loose in the city and Jane must piece together the puzzle before her, before its too late.
name: A Kiss Before Killing

description: Investigating a domestic dispute, the Dragon encounters Jennifer, a super-strong stripper who has somehow pulverised her abusive husband's entire head. Afterwards, Dragon and Alex answer a call concerning the decapitated remains of sixteen males. While almost everyone suspects Jennifer of the murders, the Dragon is soon attacked by a mysterious costumed woman, who escapes. Jennifer, who has been in jail, claims to have had nothing to do with the decapitated bodies.

Overview

By morphing his symbiotic suit to match the soldiers, Spawn infiltrates the compound where Wynn has reinforced security. He successfully severs communication and power systems to cripple the battalions, leaving a terrified Wynn trapped. Spawn threatens Wynn with the promise to undermine his operations until nothing remains of his international empire. In the alley, Sam & Twitch get no information from the bums about Spawn. Cog then fills them in on facts that create more questions.
name: Checkmate

description: Matt Murdock visits Vincent Grazia in prison and learns his identity has been compromised! To make matters worse, Mr. Fear infiltrates Ryker’s Island and floods the prison with fear gas! A riot breaks out and it’s up to Daredevil to settle the score. Can the Man Without Fear face Fear itself?
name: Prison Without Walls

description: To face the fury of the Sentinels!
name: To Face the Fury of the Sentinels!

description: Dane Whitman, A.K.A. the Black Knight, joins Oracle Inc. as a scientist/teammate, and leaps into action with the H4H against Nitro!
name: Blowup!

description:
Much to the consternation of his teammates, Wolverine has brought the unconscious Hulk to Xavier's mansion for medical aid, after the Hulk's mysterious collapse in the Savage Land. The X-Men bind him within diagnostic equipment, but he comes to and goes on a rampage, attacking the mutants.

Meanwhile, in New York City, Betty Banner receives some shocking news from her unwelcome visitor, Henry Peter Gyrich. And in Orlando, Rick Jones finds his future granddaughter, Janis, after she's had a run-in with a pair of police officers, who now lie unconscious on the sidewalk.

Back at the X-Mansion, the Hulk overwhelms the mutants and breaks out, making his way into the nearby woods. He nearly gives in to drowsiness, then realizes where he is and breaks out through the 'sky'.

Forge arrives to help, and Cable and Storm explain they lured the Hulk into the Danger Room, programmed to replicate the outdoors, then flooded the room with sleeping gas. Just then, the Hulk bursts up through the floor. Forge aims the weapon he's brought with him at the Hulk, who recognizes it as the one used by the Maestro. Forge fires it, and the Hulk vanishes.

Elsewhere, Betty goes to the location given to her by Gyrich, where she finds her father, General "Thunderbolt" Ross, previously presumed dead. Simultaneously, Hulk finds he has been teleported to the lair of his new host, Apocalypse, who is about to propose a deal to the Hulk.
name: Waiting to X-Hale

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Ka-Zar goes to the States to hunt down his brother, Parnival Plunder.
name: The Concrete Jungle

description: A classic old school battle between the Federation and the Klingon Empire.  More accurately between Captain Christopher Pike of the U.S.S. Enterprise and Commander Kaaj of the Varchas.  Kaaj is a ruthless leader killing almost as many men or more than Pike himself.  If you have ever seen a 1960's Star Trek episode you know who comes out on top.
name: The Flat, Gold Forever

description: The Thunderbolts begin getting comfortable with theirselves and eachother, but then are attacked by the Growing Man. Atlas goes face to face against the Growing Man, testing his upper limits. When the Growing Man is big enough, Techno goes inside of the synthetic being and messes with his circuits, ultimately rendering him useless. Growing Man lets out a signal from his eyes upon his defeat, which is intended to be a beacon for the nefarious Kang.
name: Growing Pains
In the Shadow of the Crime-Master

description: In Peter Parker's partnership to Black Cat/ Felicia Hardy intensifies as Spiderman, Peter Parker contemplates revealing his identity to her..with a consequence. Black Cat sets to want the world to know the hero Spiderman truly is from what the media has ruined his reputation in the past. Ben Reilley, Peter Parker's clone, also gains insight on trusting other's to his Spiderman alias.
name: The Men Behind The Mask
Dead Ahead

description:
Aiko is banish with her friends to the 'Hole' by Empress Rellapor. Poog reveals the shocking truth behind the empress' actions. 
 
Moments later the team find out why they call it the 'Hole'.

Story 1: "Revenge of the Gorgons"

Story 2: "Theft of the Young Lovelies"
Ben and Rain begin the search for Traci.
name: The Book of Law, Chapter One of Five: Digol/The Road To You, Being There: Part One

description: Kirby Hero introduces himself to Kevin Matchstick and Joe Phat by way of attacking the nest of harpies they were staking out.  Kevin and Joe join in, and the harpies are routed.  Kirby is another avatar, the Olympian.  Their slave turns out to be the seemingly-insane Wally Ut, who claims to be Kevin's second mage (replacing Mirth).  Kevin can't believe such a ridiculous figure could be his second mage.  Kevin, Kirby, and Joe, on the other hand, all get along really well, and Kirby temporarily joins the other two on their quest.  They drive off without Wally.  Meanwhile, the Pale Incanter sends his sons the Sprigginflints to find the heroes.
name: When We Three Shall Meet

description: Quantum & Woody span the globe, in search of clues to solve a tragic murder. Along the way they happen to unravel a world-threatening international conspiracy and rack up frequent flyer miles as they criss-cross the world. All this, and Woody buys a goat.
name: Yet Another Story

description: Superman defeats the mummy that the Young Heroes tackled last issue. He is offered a place on the team and when he politely refuses, Hard Drive has a screaming fit.
name: Two Hearts Beat as One Giant Undead Guy

description:
Having escaped from Black Tom [see Generation X #25], Franklin Richards, Leech, Artie Maddicks, Tana Nile, Howard the Duck and the Man-Thing now float on a chunk of earth through the Nexus of All Realities.  Tiring of Howard's complaining, Tana Nile tosses him off their 'island' and the Duck falls through one of the doorways populating the Nexus. 
Howard lands in Nevernevernarniozbia, a land that appears to be an amalgam of many storybook worlds peopled by fairy tale versions of super-heroes and villains.  The rest of the group follow through the same doorway, but are themselves followed by a living shadow called the Dark Hunter. 
The group is soon captured by a wicked version of the Scarlet Witch, then are reunited with Howard who has also been captured.  Leech negates the powers of his captors, and he and his friends almost escape, but are stopped short by the Dark Hunter.  To the shock of Howard and the rest, the Man-Thing speaks.
name: Once Upon a Time...

description: An immortal that can travel through time teams up with an heroic Native American warrior.

The Gamesman has captured Animal Man's daughter Maxine! Will Aquaman and Animal Man be able to save her?

Maxine Baker has been captured in a container at the bottom of the ocean, where she has just used the last air container she had. She then reaches out to her father Animal Man through The Red, when he answers he is hurt but she then senses someone else closer to her. In the aftermath of his battle with Triton, Aquaman has been left blinded by Poseidon, who says he will help him if he prays to him to which Aquaman promptly refuses leaving Aquaman on land far from help earning him Aquman's vengeance. Meanwhile Buddy Baker in his speed boat is blown up by his foe, as Aquaman hears this and comes searching for survivors. However his blindness proves a huge obstacle, until he runs into Topo and Buddy Baker who asks for his help.

Aquaman then charges the nearby Nemek to rescue Maxine, as Aquaman and Buddy begin a battle with the Gamesman. The two then repel the Gamesman as Nemek brings Maxine to the surface with the Gamesman fleeing and swearing vengeance on Buddy.
name: Sight Unseen

description:
Hostile robots roam the halls of the Watchtower. The League is trapped. The Key is minutes away from becoming a god. The League's only hope of survival lies in a rookie archer. Will the son of Oliver Queen help save the planet?

Each Justice League Member is dreaming their lives in an alternative live. Superman is a Green Lantern of Krypton, Batman is old and retired with Tim Drake as Batman and Bruce Wayne Jr. as Robin. It is revealed that each Member of the JLA is having their own dream due to the Key having them drugged. The only person to not be effected is Connor Hawke.

Connor is beamed up to the Moon Watchtower and find the Key and his robots all over. He takes them on single handed, getting wounded in the process. He even digs his father's old arrows out from the JLA Trophy Room to take on the advisory in an attempt to stop the Key.
name: Imaginary Stories

description:
Zero Tolerance has begun! Cable declares war!

After the X-Men were captured, the Xavier Institute fell under Bastion´s control and surrounded by Zero Tolerance´s First Strike. Cable starts attacking their forces solo, so they cannot use some vital information that was held on protocols Xavier.

This comic is part of Operation: Zero Tolerance.
name: Moving Target Part One: No Escape

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Deadpool brings Typhiod Mary to the Hellhouse, in order to help her get work so she can pay him for breaking her out of the crazy house. T-Ray is not pleased by this. This is because Typhiod and T-Ray have a past. This gives T-Ray another reason for T-Ray to hate old Deady so he burns off his mask. Deadpool freaks out and runs out of the Hellhouse screaming "my face!". He runs arounf frantically trying to find somethign to hide his face before someone sees it. He finds a young woman's laundry line and makes a make-shift mask from her clothes. The woman catches him with her clothes to his face and she assumes the worst. On accident during this occurrence Deadpool knocks Mary out the window and she has memories flooding back to her that were long forgotten while she was in the Asylum. And these memories will take them to New York City to visit an old buddy of hers...
name: Typhoid...It Ain't Just fer Cattle Any More or Head Trips or Head Jobs

description:
With X-Men missing… Marrow goes wild! And Spider-Man makes a special appearance!

Not trusting the television reports about the X-Men attacking Operation Zero Tolerance aircraft, J. Jonah Jameson assigns his staff to get the true story; Jameson may not care for costumed super-beings, but he hates government supported witch-hunts and civil right violations even more. Peter Parker has been assigned to get photos of Henry Peter Gyrich, whom he finds under attack by Callisto and Marrow.

In an interlude on a distant planet, Gambit wonders how he and his fellow X-Men will get home.

Back at the Daily Bugle, Jameson is visited by Bastion, who offers the publisher a disc containing many of the X-Men's secrets.

On the streets nearby, Spider-Man's fight with Callisto and Marrow gets complicated when Gyrich's bodyguards reveal themselves as Prime Sentinels. Callisto is stunned, but Gyrich and two arriving police officers gun down the Sentinels. Marrow tries to attack Gyrich, but Spider-Man talks her down, and she departs, carrying Callisto's unconscious form.

Back in Jameson's office, the publisher refuses Bastion's offer, telling the mutant hunter he trusts him not one bit, and he destroys Bastion's disc.
name: The Story of the Year!

description:
PKNA #8

Silicio / Silicon
name: Silicio

description: Superman and Madman have swapped powers. Angry, hyper-powered feminists have taken over City Hall. The streets are full of hungry zombies. There's only one fella' who could create these problems, and it's up to Superman and Madman to put an end to his escapades! But how . . . ? Mike Allred turns his talents toward comics greatest superhero in the conclusion to this three-issue crossover! Co-published with DC Comics.
name: Super Madness

description: Luse goes on trail as the Blood Guard ambushes Cassy.
name: One: Your Funeral My Trial

description: Fone Bone and Smiley trek into the Eastern Mountains to set free the baby Rat Creature, who Smiley names Bartleby, and accidentally encounter the two Stupid Rat Creatures. During an effort to ditch the two, they encounter the giant mountain lion Roque Ja. Roque Ja finds the Bones familiar, knowing that the Hooded One is searching for one of them. He explains the Hooded One fears “the one who bears the star” (meaning Phoney Bone) will rise as a new leader and unite the valley against him. However, Roque Ja remains taciturn about whose side he is on.
name: Roque Ja

description: "Man and Machine!" Part 2 of 2. Guest-starring Donna Troy. It's the ultimate battle of man vs. machine as Green Lantern tests his mettle against the brand new techno threat of the Machine Messiah. Plus, Donna Troy receives some startling and tragic news.
name: Man & Machine

deck: Mattie and Silver Banshee merge into one woman, and the results aren't too good for Supergirl.
description: Silver Banshee takes over Mattie, and goes to kill the man who killed Mattie's brother. Supergirl stops her; Dick's cancer is cured, as Buzz promised.
name: Cries In The Darkness

description: Just how many ways can you kill the Resurrection Man? His wife and best friend are out to find out, and they're not going to stop until they do. Meanwhile, Hooker is on the scene, planning to take Mitch's last remains for his own horrifying use.
name: Scorpion Memories, Part 2

description: Soames found Scarecrow tied up - he'd told Nightwing everything he knew. Redhorn fired Soames from the police department after learning things. Soames attacked Blockbuster, but had his head twisted and neck snapped by Desmond in "self defense." Desmond sustained 6 gunshot wounds in the attack.
name: Fear Takes Flight

description: Brainiac 5 needs the world's most advanced computers, which leads him and the Legion right to the high-tech insides of the fabulous Metal Men—and their remarkable Responsometers! Unfortunately, Brainy doesn't realize that the robot heroes are actually much more than robots.
name: The Emerald Doom!

description: The great executioner Nexus killed his father! That's not news to Nexus readers, but it's a revelation for his followers, the people of Ylum. They turn against the once-mighty Nexus, and all those connected to him -- including Sundra Peale, who is in the midst of a presidential race. And that is when the great executioner contemplates his own end.

It's a quiet, cold day at the crossroads between the old year and the new one, and Nuala receives an unexpected invitation from the Dreaming, while her brother weighs a surprising challenge from his nemesis.
name: Ice
The Assassin

description: En route to an awards banquet, Steel and Amanda are assaulted by corrupt cops, his jet boots are stolen, and then he's subjected to the chaotic war zone known as the GSMC emergency room.
name: Trauma

description:
The Key has locked the Justice League into all new realities. Slowly, surely the League is escaping...and this is exactly what the villain wants!

The JLA are all trapped in their own realities that have been brought on by the Key. Green Arrow (Connor Hawke) is desperately trying to save them but it is only him and his father's old trick arrows against the Key and a group of highly advanced Robots.

In their dreamworlds each JLA member starts to realize that they are being manipulated. Just as the team starts to gather together Green Arrow takes out the Key with the punching-glove arrow. With this Green Arrow confirms him membership in the league. The Key is put in a mind prison in a hospital leaving him in a comma-like state. The issue ends with the shadowy lit Injustice Gangs and evil doppelgangers of the JLA.
name: Elseworlds

description: The life of a hero...six decades in the making. Shortly after the United States' entry into WW II the young Bart Simms, heir to an industrial fortune, makes a discovery that will change his life forever and the course of history along with it. A cache of mysterious electronic equipment hidden within his father's factory, within it a fully loaded state-of-the art computer manufactured by Angel Computers... in 1998! Loaded with schematics for technology not yet invented and records of events not yet happened, Bart sees this as his opportunity to aid the Allied war effort. Armed with weapons from the future he becomes Doctor Tomorrow, a self-proclaimed time traveler journeyed back in time to ensure history keeps to its proper course.
name: Age of Tomorrow

description: Linda Meechum is getting married! So what do Colin King, terrorists, and a giant stone Chow-Chow dog have to do with Denny's sister's wedding?

OverviewThe notes of Dr. Victor von Frankenstein, the greatest scientific mind of the nineteenth century, have fallen into the hands of the greatest scientific mind of the twentieth century, Thomas Edison. Tarzan is determined that Edison will not repeat the mistakes of the late Dr. Frankenstein . . . but there's a hulking beast that has his own stake in all of this!
name: The Modern Prometheus (Part 2 of 2)

description: We continue to follow the sword, Grasscutter, through history. It's April of 1185, and the great civil war of Japan is nearing an end. At the Battle of Dannoura, The Heike Clan find themselves surrounded by the Genji. The victors will have all of Japan at their command. The Heike still have hope -- they still have the sword of the Gods.
name: Grasscutter, Prologue 4: Dan-no-ura

description:
The Joker and the Demon Etrigan have almost succeeded in their plan to bring Hell to Gotham City, and the Dark Knight has just one slim chance to stop them.

Batman caused Etrigan to realize that Joker was not a sorcerer; he was using the demon. Batman saved Joker from Etrigan's wrath and delivered him to the police. The demon vanished.
name: Major Arcana, Part 3: Hell to Pay
